AUDIO: 'all scary because it\'s in Python format, you can easily read the English to see how their prompt enhancers work. If you want to write better prompts, you can either follow their instructions manually or you can add something like'

[04:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'an Ollama note to do the prompt enhancing for you. If you\'re wondering just what Bernini can do, then take a look at these options because it can do a lot of things. Text to image, text to video, image to video, video editing,'

[05:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and a whole load more. Now, I\'ve put all these capabilities into a single workflow because I like everything in one place, rather than loading lots of different things with a length of one, you\'ll get a single image, which is'

[05:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ideal not only for image editing, but also if you want to see the first frame of your video will actually do what you\'re asking it to do before you commit to however many frames it is that you'

[05:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'want. 5 seconds or 81 frames is the typical length, but as mentioned, you can go longer if you like. CFG one and six steps means you won\'t be waiting too'

[05:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'long, usually around 30 seconds or so, depending of course on the resolution you have chosen and other factors such as your own hardware. Because there are so many options you can use nodes such as the fast group'

[05:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'bypass or muters which is to enable or disable the various named groups. I\'ve got them set up here for source and reference videos, up to four images, and various ways you can save things. The'

[06:11] [scene:talk]
